### Proposal (Obs #3676)
Versioned SQLite schema upgrade path. Replaces single `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` bootstrap with a migration runner in `internal/infra/sqlite`. Scope: migration runner, `schema_migrations` table, baseline version 1 for fresh and existing DBs.

### Spec (Obs #3679)
8 requirements: Fresh Database Baseline, Existing Current-Schema Baseline (2 scenarios), Migration Version Table, Idempotent Open, Ordered Transactional Application, Failure Rollback, Layer Isolation, Clear Error Reporting. Compliance: 8/9 compliant, 1 partial (Clear Error Reporting — bootstrap/current-version/commit paths statically wrapped but not directly induced).

### Design (Obs #3680)
Replace `schema.sql` exec with embedded SQL migrations via `embed.FS`. `NNNN_name.sql` convention, `schema_migrations` table with version/name/applied_at. One tx per migration, abort on first error. Baseline detection via `sqlite_master` probe. 7 architecture decisions recorded.

